In this article, it is stated that President Obama spoke with President Francois Hollande of France, Chancellor Angela Merkel of Germany, and Prime Minister David Cameron of the United Kingdom to discuss the political framework reached between the P5+1, the EU, and Iran on a Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action (JCPOA) regarding Iran's nuclear program. The leaders expressed gratitude to each other for their roles in negotiating this historic step and agreed that the framework represents significant progress towards a comprehensive solution that prevents Iran from obtaining a nuclear weapon and ensures the peaceful nature of Iran's nuclear program in the future.